<br>
But trouble makers were trouble makers and a few less friends made little difference in the grand scheme of her plan. She wasn’t above &quot;getting her hands dirty&quot; and rather quite enjoyed it as a test of her abilities. To be ruthless, cunning and successful in taking the lives of those troublemakers merely set the stage for what was to come. <br>
<br>
The unexpected stage two was complete and she could move forward with her plan as originally intended. <br>
<br>
The first phase was to find a long forgotten project which was still funded and supported, at least on paper, by Omni-Tek. A major corporation the size of Omni-Tek had volumes of these cases and projects long forgotten, waiting to be closed or set in motion. Any industrious person who could get themselves placed in charge of one of those projects could easily find themselves on the fast track toward financial and career success. <br>
<br>
It was all a matter of finding the right project. <br>
<br>
Some of the projects were forgotten for a reason. Foolish and inane could best describe some of those projects, funded simply because someone had a friend high up the corporate ladder. Or, and more likely, that someone had uncovered some dirt on said corporate official and got a nothing project funded simply to live a life of ease, showing up to work to play holo-games while collecting fat payrolls. A few years go by and the whole affair, including the project, is lost and forgotten like the culture of an ancient alien race. The automated human resources department continues to write checks that simply disappear against the vast volume of the Omni-Tek budget. <br>
<br>
But some projects were brilliant. Some were cut down and forgotten intentionally. Such was the case of the project Natasha had uncovered. She looked at the title again and smiled. <br>
<br>
Codename: Darkness <br>
<br>
The Darkness program was created a hundred years ago by a dedicated and radical man named Decker. But Decker’s project stepped on the toes of a bureaucrat who headed a similar project, but far less effective and with a far greater budget. The bureaucrat had Decker assassinated… or at least Natasha believed that is what happened. The Darkness project quickly disappeared just as Decker had. Over the years, the bureaucrat died and slowly his project was closed down. Now Darkness was a ripe gem waiting for someone to run it. <br>
<br>
All Natasha had to do was to get herself appointed to run the Darkness Project. <br>
<br>
The mantra of the Darkness project stood out on the page as Natasha schemed. &quot;Complete Eradication: Zero Retaliation Acceptable.&quot; Darkness was a covert operations commission that allowed Decker to higher highly skilled assassins, cyber-jockies, spies, agents and soldiers of many talents to take the fight to the heart of the Clan rebels, leaving Omni-Tek standing unhindered to expand across the wastes of Rubi-ka, creating an ideal society for every citizen. <br>
<br>
It was a beautiful vision. <br>
<br>
It was an achievable dream provided she could find fanatical and devoted soldiers to work within the autonomy that Darkness provided. It was the autonomy that made Darkness perfect. It would keep Darkness out of the bureaucratic red tape, answering only to the laws of Omni-Tek… and most of those could be compromised given sufficient proof of successful anti-clan activities. With the proper planing, strikes could be made by Darkness, completely destroying a given objective. <br>
<br>
&quot;Complete Eradication: Zero Retaliation Acceptable.&quot; Natasha mulled over the mantra. It was a good idea, in theory. But no plan is perfect. Something can always go wrong. &quot;Complete Eradication&quot; seemed rather redundant to her. She figured she could eliminate the &quot;Complete&quot; in the title and leave &quot;Eradication: Zero Retaliation Acceptable.&quot; Though, she figured there was a better mantra out there… but that was hardly important at this time.  However, she did like the acronym better. E.Z.R.A. <br>
<br>
Natasha smiled. Tomorrow night she would launch phase three on an unsuspecting bureaucrat and would take on her codename as the leader of Darkness. Ezra! <br>
<br>
