<br>
Demetra was a Meta-physist. A spiritualist for the modern age. A Techno-Shaman, as someone once said and it had stuck in her mind.  A Street Priest who understood the inner-workings of big city culture, which was like a living, breathing organism unto itself with each individual like a cell making up the whole. <br>
<br>
But some might say it was the thrill of the nightlife, fast and furious living, every bit as addictive as any drug that could be purchased on the streets.  Each ally was its own world, with its own rules, gangs and leaders.<br>
<br>
Demetra loved it all.  The good as well as the bad, from the lowliest, half dead, drug abuser strung out on meta-meth to the most cultured aristocrat living in their sky high penthouse who pissed over the edge because they could get away with anything.  <br>
<br>
Demetra glanced back into her hand.  She was intrigued by a small card she got from a “runner” earlier this evening.<br>
<br>
“Do you want to do your part?”  Was all the card had written on it.  On the back was an address of a corporate office and the name “Ezra” signed below.<br>
