<br>
But nothing would stop her from her goal. If it meant pandering to the base instincts of men who could shape her destiny, then nothing would stop her from doing so. <br>
<br>
Then the door slid open and the older bureaucratic gentleman stood before her in only a silken bath robe with a wry &quot;cat to a mouse&quot; grin on his face. <br>
<br>
&quot;Come in my pet.&quot; He said in a lower register than he normally spoke with. <br>
<br>
Natasha slinked into the room, the satin-silk fibers of her dress shimmering as they conformed to the movements of her body. The bureaucrat emitted a soft growl as she passed by, as if it were a prelude to a night of wild, animalistic pleasure. She quietly hoped her dress would not betray her by highlighting her crawling skin. She flashed him a wry smile of her own and sauntered strait to the bar. <br>
<br>
He was all to eager to pour her a drink, taking it as a sign of abandoning the restraints of the office-place. She simply needed something to help calm her nerves. She absolutely had to be in control of herself, there was simply too much at stake. She thought about the cards she had sent out to various &quot;elements&quot; that she felt would be needed to build the Darkness project and now felt foolish at having jumped the gun. She had not yet gotten the project. But Natasha had been extremely confident. <br>
<br>
The bureaucrat spoke unendingly about himself and his current projects. He even went so far as to toss out the possibility of Natasha getting a raise and working more closely with him. In a way, Natasha felt sorry for him. He was a moderately attractive man but age and stress had begun to show in his face. His &quot;salt and pepper&quot; hair was thinning in an unattractive way and he was obviously over weight from drinking too much and eating too many fatty foods despite the miraculous fat burning products on the market. She knew he had been in several failed marriages due to the pressures of his job. He was high enough on the corporate ladder to have great power, but not high enough to trust his underlings to complete the work satisfactorily and spent many long nights toiling over case notes, memos, and reports. <br>
<br>
Natasha actually enjoyed the hard work and welcomed the opportunity to put herself into that kind of position. But she did not want a job like he had. Power he certainly had. But he did not have the ability to pave his own road, so to speak, where his career was concerned. Directives were passed down the ladder through him and reports were analyzed and then forwarded to those who would make actual decisions on the knowledge he passed upwards. She wanted to be the one providing the direction in her little slice of Omni-Tek. <br>
<br>
He paused. <br>
<br>
Natasha knew it was the time that he would make his move. Quickly, just as he began to rise from his seat, she placed her foot in his crotch, holding him down. Surprise slowly turned to a devilish grin as his fingers eagerly glided over her ankle, then sliped the sandal-like shoe off. His fingers worked her soft flesh as he massaged her foot. It felt wonderful. <br>
<br>
&quot;Have I been a bad boy?&quot; He asked slyly. <br>
<br>
&quot;As a matter of fact, you have.&quot; Natasha answered as she slipped her hand slowly to a broach pinned to her shoulder. She removed the broach, watching his eyes light up as he expected to watch the dress begin to fall away from her body. But the broach was holding something intact other than her dress. She flipped open a small compartment and pulled out a tiny holo emitter. <br>
<br>
&quot;Dirty pictures?&quot; He asked, hopefully. <br>
<br>
&quot;Yes.&quot; She answered and flipped the emitter on and began cycling through the images. Suddenly he realized what the pictures were. <br>
<br>
&quot;You bitch.&quot; He growled, jumping to his feet. &quot;Stupid little girl. Do you think to blackmail me?&quot; He asked, glancing again at the images of him in compromising sexual activities. <br>
<br>
Natasha smiled. <br>
<br>
&quot;You should have done your homework, bitch. I am not currently married or in a position that your stupid sexual pictures can damage me.&quot; He growled at her, taking on a different kind of predator-like look than he had earlier this night. <br>
<br>
&quot;Look again.&quot; Natasha said softly. <br>
<br>
He looked at the holos more carefully. Suddenly he realized what … no, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> who</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the holos were of. A year ago, company picnic, high ranking corporate official going through rough times with his wife. Wife decides to get back at her husband by seducing him. They realize their bad judgement only too late. He thought it was buried in the past. <br>
<br>
&quot;It does me no good what so ever for you to loose your job over this.&quot; Natasha said reassuringly as she watched his face sour. <br>
<br>
&quot;What do you want.&quot; He growls, looking at her with hate in his eyes… the predator now caged. <br>
<br>
&quot;Nothing really, nothing that will harm you in any way. I want you to assign me to head the Darkness project.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Darkness? Never heard of it.&quot; He says, liking the sound of the payoff. <br>
<br>
&quot;No, of course not. It is about 100 years old.&quot; She says, pulling out a computer memory crystal and handing it to him. &quot;You can claim it as a quality check. You found the program without a leader and assigned me to verify the program or close it. Simple as that. It is a win-win situation. If the program goes well, you are merited for the quality check. If it fails, then you successfully close a useless program wasting company creds for nearly a century.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Is that all?&quot; He asks, feeling relieved by the proposition. <br>
<br>
&quot;That and remember, I still have the originals of these.&quot; She says, indicating the holos. &quot;Don’t screw with me so I have any reason to screw with you.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;I am glad we could settle this peacefully. You are a sharp woman. Is there anything I can do to help your new project, Director Dupaski?&quot; He asks regaining a bit of his frisky composure. <br>
<br>
&quot;Not yet. But if you really want to help, I am sure there are things that can be done that will mutually benefit both our careers.&quot; She said as she stood. <br>
<br>
&quot;You don’t have to leave yet.&quot; He cooed. <br>
<br>
&quot;Yes I do. A girl cant give up all of her aces in one night.&quot; She purred back then sauntered out of the door.<br>
<br>
<br>
