<br>
Demetra seemed to optimize everything Natasha hated on the seedier side of life in Omni controlled cities.  Her general look spoke of rebellion.  She had the look of both cheep hooker with her long black trench coat contrasting the garish white face paint (with black highlights) and fish-net stockings, yet she carried herself with the statuesque grace of authority.  Demetra’s eyes were knowing and piercing.  She looked around the room as if taking in every nook and niche then filed the information away for later use.  <br>
<br>
Natasha saw more to the woman standing before her than her appearance let on.  Demetra looked at Natasha and raised an eyebrow.  <br>
<br>
“Come, sit down.  Let us talk.”  Natasha said evenly.  Demetra crossed over to the chair before Natasha’s plasti-oak desk and dropped into it rather ungracefully.  <br>
<br>
“What’s my part?”  Demetra said looking Natasha strait in the eyes.<br>
<br>
“My name is Ezra.”  Natasha began her well rehearsed speech which told of the Darkness project.  She studied Demetra’s reactions as she spoke, but the woman was emotionless, like an old 200 model android.  The complete lack of output from the gothic woman told Natasha a great deal about her practiced control and secretive nature.   All of the research Natasha had done on Demetra was confirmed.  Natasha was very thorough.  <br>
<br>
“So.” Demetra said at the conclusion of Natasha’s speech.  “You want me to be your ‘right arm,’ is that what you are asking me?”<br>
<br>
“I did not say that.”  Natasha said evenly.  <br>
<br>
“Yes you did.  You said it with your eyes.  You want me.  And in more ways than just the Darkness project.”<br>
<br>
